msContents.summary: Volume from a 14th-century copy of a 10th-century dictionary of the Arabic language. Words are indexed by their last root letter, with this volume covering the letters za' to lam. Marginal notes by a reader and proofreader. Later pastedown on inner cover has remedies written in Arabic and Persian.

msItem.title: Section of Tāj al-lughah wa-ṣiḥāḥ al-ʻArabīyah
msItem.author: Jawharī, Ismāʻīl ibn Ḥammād, d. 1003?

supportDesc.extent: 203 leaves : 269 x 172 (198 x 125) mm. bound to 269 x 180 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated title page (f. 1r) in Mamluk style; significant words in red.

binding.p: Repaired leather, blind-stamped center medallion and cornerpieces.

origin.p: Written in Egypt or Syria in the 14th century.

history.provenance: Ownership stamps on title page canceled (f. 1r).
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Nov. 2000.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
